Metadata.Title: The Cyber-Terrorists I
Metadata.Description: Our client has described these 5 targets as a part of the largest cyber-terrorism group. Marcelo Faravelli and Fabio Pavione are the founders and were the lead hitmen for the 1997 attack on Eitan Sharevi, an Israeli businessman who was assassinated because he had incriminating evidence of the group, which is called NMGI. Mario Saltatore led the group into blackmailing 200 government officials. Sebastiano Noce and Reginaldo Neglia have attempted to blackmail ICA. Eliminate them and extract.
